		<title>New Release: Custom Post Types, Scheduled Publishing and more</title>
		<link>http://kapost.com/new-release-custom-post-types-scheduled-publishing-and-more/</link>
		<comments>http://kapost.com/new-release-custom-post-types-scheduled-publishing-and-more/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 28 Sep 2011 20:53:44 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>MIke Lewis</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://kapost.com/new-release-custom-post-types-scheduled-publishing-and-more/</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[We&#8217;re excited to announce our latest release today! The first upgraded feature is the New &#8220;Create Post&#8221; button: The &#8220;Create New&#8221; button at the very top right side of Kapost has been updated to be cleaner. It&#8217;s the same button, &#8230; <a href="http://kapost.com/new-release-custom-post-types-scheduled-publishing-and-more/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>
<ol> </ol>
</div>
<div>We&#8217;re excited to announce our latest release today!</p>
<p>The first upgraded feature is the <strong>New &#8220;Create Post&#8221; button:<br /></strong></div>
<div>The &#8220;Create New&#8221; button at the very top right side of Kapost has been updated to be cleaner. It&#8217;s the same button, just looks different.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="http://kapost.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/new_post_button.png" alt="" /></p>
<div>The second feature is <strong>Scheduled Publishing: </strong><br /><strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />This feature allows you to schedule a post to be published in the future, instead of manually choosing to publish each post. &nbsp;Once it is scheduled, it can still be edited and adjusted but when that time rolls around, the post will be pushed to live, onto your publication.</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p></div>
<div><img src="http://kapost.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/mockup_2.png" alt="" /></p>
</div>
<div>The third feature is <strong>Custom Post Types:<br /></strong></div>
<div>
<div>Custom Post types is a feature that is highly customizable and part of our effort to enable editorial teams to fit their product workflow. In the custom fields area in Settings (in your Kapost newsroom) has been moved to a new tab.&nbsp; </p>
<p>The main part of this feature is that if you want all your posts to have another date field, or another image field, or be a top ten list post this is now possible.&nbsp; </p>
<p><img src="http://kapost.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/mockup_3.png" alt="" /></p>
<p>If you have any questions at all, please don&#8217;t hesitate to reach out.</p></div>
</div>
