		<title>Content Marketing World Recap</title>
		<link>http://kapost.com/content-marketing-world-recap/</link>
		<comments>http://kapost.com/content-marketing-world-recap/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 13 Sep 2011 17:30:19 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>Grace Boyle</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Events and Conferences]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://kapost.com/content-marketing-world-recap/</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Last week, Toby and I flew into Cleveland for the first annual, Content Marketing World conference. With over 16 countries represented and 600+ attendees, we were excited to be part of this growing industry and group. We had our first &#8230; <a href="http://kapost.com/content-marketing-world-recap/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Last week, Toby and I flew into Cleveland for the first annual, <a href="http://www.contentmarketingworld.com/">Content Marketing World </a>conference. With over 16 countries represented and 600+ attendees, we were excited to be part of this growing industry and group.</p>
<p>We had our first booth in the exhibitor hall and also, presented at their Technology Cage Match, which included closing with a haiku on what Kapost does!</p>
<p><em><img class="aligncenter" src="http://kapost.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/tobypresenting.jpg" alt="" width="212" height="355" /></em></p>
<p>I&#8217;ve included some photos here (note on the go phone photos) and some informational highlights.</p>
<p><img src="http://kapost.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/tobycmw.jpg" alt="" width="550" height="420" /></p>
<p><img src="http://kapost.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/tobyandgrace.jpg" alt="" width="556" height="413" /><br />
<em></em></p>
<p>Speaker Highlights:</p>
<blockquote><p><strong>From Sally Hogshead:</strong></p>
<p>A study from BBC showed that due to web browsing, our attention spans have shortened. Our attention span used to be 20 minutes long and over generations it is now 9 seconds.</p>
<p>How do you stand out? The best idea doesn&#8217;t win if no one pays attention in the first place. It doesn&#8217;t matter how great your blog is, if no one reads it. It&#8217;s not about being the best, it&#8217;s about finding a way to take who you are and create a relationship that is captivating.</p>
<p>Rebellion is the root of all creativity.<strong></strong></p>
<p>David Meerman Scott:</p>
<p>The most overused in English language, used in press releases is: <em>innovate</em>.When referring to &#8220;real time&#8221; he states: Don&#8217;t use stock photos. Use real employees on your website. Use real people to represent real people and REAL language. Always think about the second paragraph of the story. <strong></strong></p>
<p>Jay Baer:</p>
<p>The future of marketing is helping, not selling.</p>
<p>Coined: Friend of mine awareness. You build an inside circle of trust by <em>helping</em> consumers.</p>
<p><strong>Brian Clark, Copyblogger:</strong></p>
<p>Be reader focused. Don&#8217;t take for granted that people will pay attention to you. Everything needs to be reader friendly.</p>
<p>Number one mistake in creating content is not focusing enough on the audience&#8217;s needs.</p></blockquote>
<p><strong>Personal highlights: </strong></p>
<p>Opening night at Rock N&#8217; Roll Hall of Fame on the water. With delicious appetizers and drinks, we mingled among the greats and toured the famed museum.</p>
<p>Kevin Smith, (aka Silent Bob) stand-up at a comedy club, which was really a personalized Q&amp;A. He also was the <a href="http://www.contentmarketinginstitute.com/2011/09/kevin-smith/">closing keynote for the conference.</a> One of the funniest guys, who you can tell, is brilliant and privvy to the online world and business.</p>
<p>We had a great time and met many people in the industry. We&#8217;re looking forward to more converastions and continuing to help fill a need for content marketers.<br />
<!-- BEGIN KAPOST ANALYTICS CODE --></p>
