		<description><![CDATA[As we get to know our customers better, we listen closely to their pain points.  Sometimes it&#8217;s managing their editorial calendar, other times it&#8217;s being able to message many users at once. One item we have consistently heard to be &#8230; <a href="http://kapost.com/new-feature-invoices/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>As we get to know our customers better, we listen closely to their pain points.  Sometimes it&#8217;s managing their editorial calendar, other times it&#8217;s being able to message many users at once.</p>
<p>One item we have consistently heard to be a big source of pain is<strong> invoicing.</strong></p>
<p>Editors often face trouble with invoicing around formatting, freelancers send in different versions of invoices, receiving verification of the posts and finally, getting them in on time.</p>
<p><strong>That said, we&#8217;re happy to announce that today, we&#8217;re solving this problem as we&#8217;ve released a <span style="text-decoration: underline;">new invoicing feature</span> within Kapost.  </strong></p>
<p>This is how it works:</p>
<p>Any post that has a payment on it is listed in a transactions table. When you&#8217;re looking at that table of posts, you can select any of them and click &#8220;Create Invoice&#8221;. Doing so will list those posts in an invoice and list the invoice in the new &#8220;Invoice&#8221; sub-tab.</p>
<p>For organizational purposes, that invoice must then be confirmed by both the Editor and the Contributor.  Once that is done, the invoice is &#8220;Completed.&#8221;</p>
<p>Any invoice that is completed can be printed and paid by your own accounting department or you can pay it directly in Kapost using PayPal.  If you pay inside Kapost, we&#8217;ll keep a record of the payment for you to always find and refer to.</p>
<p>If you&#8217;d like to see it quickly in action, check out this video:</p>
<p><iframe width="560" height="345" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/iTWWRZ3QnRc?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>
<p>We know this is a big issue and hopefully this starts to make the invoicing process less daunting and scary.  Furthermore, we have some more features in the queue, such as auto-creating invoices and adding arbitrary amounts.</p>
<p>Please let us know what you think about our new invoicing feature!<br />
